column4: If I do not have enough time to do everything, I do not worry about it.
column6: I do not tend to worry about things.
column8: I know I should not worry about things, but I just cannot help it.
column9: When I am under pressure I worry a lot.
column10: I am always worrying about something.
column11: I find it easy to dismiss worrisome thoughts
column12: As soon as I finish one task, I start to worry about everything else I have to do.
column14: When there is nothing more I can do about a concern, I do not worry about it any more.
column15: I have been a worrier all my life.
column16: I notice that I have been worrying about things.
column17: Once I start worrying, I cannot stop.
column19: I worry about projects until they are all done.
